SIMPLE: marketplace
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: marketplace
<hw>marketplace</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an area in a town
where a public market is set up; a <cref>market place</cref>; a
<er>market</er>{2}.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mart.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The commercial activity whereby good and services
are exchanged; <as>as, without competition there would be no
<ex>market</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> market.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The mechanism by which one finds a person to whom to
sell or from whom to buy goods; the opportunity to buy and sell; a
<er>market</er>{3}; <as>as, to put one's goods on the
<ex>market</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marketing</ent>⟦br⟧
